One of the University of Alberta's oldest underclassmen is a 60-year-old man who's come back to school to study the cancer that ended his wife's life.

Powel Crosley's wife Sladjana died in 2009 at the age of 58 due to granulosa, a rare form of ovarian cancer.

Only 5 per cent of ovarian cancer cases are diagnosed as granulosa.

CBS News reports Crosely spent his career to now in information technology, and enrolled in cllege again in 2010.

